---
import DocsLayout from "../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Built-in Agents" active="agents">
  <h1>Built-in Agents</h1>
  <p class="lead">
    AXIS ships with built-in support for every major AI coding agent that speaks the Agent Client
    Protocol (ACP), plus the native Claude Code and Codex CLIs.
  </p>

  <p>
    Reference an agent by name in your <code>axis.config.json</code>:
  </p>
  <pre><code>{`{
  "agents": ["claude-code", "codex"]
}`}</code></pre>

  <p>
    Many agents are bring-your-own-key (BYOK) and accept several provider environment variables;
    those rows link to the agent's own provider docs.
  </p>

  <p>
    Agents with <strong>Auto Install: yes</strong> are distributed as npm packages and AXIS will
    run them via <code>npx --yes</code> if the CLI is not already on your <code>PATH</code>.
    Agents with <strong>no</strong> ship through brew, cargo, uv, pip, or vendor installers, and
    must be installed manually before AXIS can run them.
  </p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Agent</th>
        <th>Auto Install</th>
        <th>Required Env Vars</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>claude-code</code></td>
        <td>yes</td>
        <td><code>ANTHROPIC_API_KEY</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>codex</code></td>
        <td>yes</td>
        <td><code>CODEX_API_KEY</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
